<subSubSection id="9543C83C8CEF27AA2F0B5DE7231E651E" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="557D2C2EC4DFB732FB153FF8DC0C33CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="59D6333B9DF445789BD21C969A5B2799" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
The coordinates in the original description were incorrectly recorded; latitude and longitude were swopped, and it should be 29°E instead of 39°S. Subsequent to the original description, at which time 
<taxonomicName id="81EA847969D85E3AAA7C9F110F450B00" authorityName="Herbert &amp; Kilburn" authorityYear="1986" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Rimula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Rimula rhips" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="rhips">
<emphasis id="4A347D496D7AA9F7EE7E0961DFE7A895" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Rimula rhips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was only known by a single specimen, this species has been collected between 40 and 128 m deep up to Boteler Point, 
<geoCoordinate id="724891C1F8BDF17E4C358B27B2267310" degrees="27" direction="south" minutes="01.1" orientation="latitude" precision="92" value="-27.018333">27°01.1'S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="1662A9EFD170C0857CD96A57A9EBA266" degrees="32" direction="east" minutes="55.2" orientation="longitude" precision="92" value="32.92">32°55.2'E</geoCoordinate>
, close to the border between South Africa and Mozambique.
</paragraph>
